Class AdobeAssetPSDFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.asset.AdobeAssetInternal

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class AdobeAssetPSDFile
extends com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.AdobeAssetFileInternal
    AdobeAssetPSDFile represents a Photoshop Document (PSD file). It provides methods for reading PSD previews and composites from PSD files, creating PSD files from composites, and getting layer renditions from PSD files.

      • createWithPSDComposite

        public static AdobeAssetPSDFile createWithPSDComposite(AdobePSDComposite psdComposite,
                                                       boolean overwriteExisting,
                                                       IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobeAssetPSDFile,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> psdFileCallback,
                                                       android.os.Handler callBackRequiredForHandler)
        Create a PSD file by asynchronously pushing a PSD composite structure to Adobe Creative Cloud. This operation performs a pushPSDComposite operation on the returned AdobeAssetPSDFile instance, which can then be used to either change the request priority or to cancel it.
        Parameters:
        psdComposite - the PSD composite used to create the PSD file on Adobe Creative Cloud.
        overwriteExisting - in the case of a new PSD composite whether it should overwrite an already existing composite. Set this to YES if a previous push has failed with an AdobeDCXErrorCompositeAlreadyExists.
        psdFileCallback - informs the client of PSD asset file creation related events.
        callBackRequiredForHandler - optional parameter. If not null the callback gets posted on the handler event queue.
        Returns:
        the AdobeAssetPSDFile object.

      • pushPSDComposite

        public void pushPSDComposite(AdobePSDComposite psdComposite,
                             boolean overwriteExisting,
                             IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobePSDComposite,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> psdCompositeCallback,
                             android.os.Handler callBackRequiredForHandler)
        Pushes (i.e., saves) the PSD composite object, including any modifications, to Adobe Creative Cloud asynchronously. The PSD composite is converted back into a PSD file and saved to this file's href location.
        Parameters:
        psdComposite - the PSD composite for the Creative Cloud file to be pushed back to the cloud.
        overwriteExisting - in the case of a new PSD composite whether it should overwrite an already existing composite. Set this to YES if a previous push has failed with an AdobeDCXErrorCompositeAlreadyExists error. Notice that this method will fail if overwrite is YES but there is nothing to overwrite.
        psdCompositeCallback - informs the client of PSD composite related events.
        callBackRequiredForHandler - optional parameter. If not null the callback gets posted on the handler event queue.

      • pushPSDComposite

        public boolean pushPSDComposite(AdobePSDComposite psdComposite,
                                boolean overwriteExisting)
        Pushes (i.e., saves) the PSD composite object, including any modifications, to Adobe Creative Cloud. The PSD composite will be converted back into a PSD file and saved to the file's href location.
        Parameters:
        psdComposite - the PSD composite for this cloud file to be push back to the cloud.
        overwriteExisting - in the case of a new PSD composite whether it should overwrite an already existing composite. Set this to true if a previous push has failed with an AdobeDCXErrorCompositeAlreadyExists error. Notice that this method will fail if overwrite is true but there is nothing to overwrite.
        Returns:
        value indicating whether or not the push operation succeeded.

      • getRenditionForLayer

        public java.lang.String getRenditionForLayer(java.lang.Integer layerID,
                                             java.lang.Integer layerCompID,
                                             AdobeAssetFileRenditionType renditionType,
                                             AdobeAssetImageDimensions dimensions,
                                             IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<byte[],com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> dataDelegate,
                                             android.os.Handler callBackRequiredForHandler)
        Gets a rendition of a layer in the PSD asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        layerID - the ID of the layer for which a rendition should be generated. Pass nil to render the entire PSD.
        layerCompID - the ID of the layerComp which should be applied. Pass nil to apply the default layerComp.
        renditionType - the type of rendition to request.
        dimensions - the dimensions of the rendition in 'points'. The value gets adjusted to pixels depending on the screen resolution. The largest of the dimensions' width and height sets the bounds for the rendition size (width and height).
        dataDelegate - the callback interface provides events related to rendition request.
        callBackRequiredForHandler - optional parameter. If not null the callback gets posted on the handler event queue.
        Returns:
        the token for the request that can be used to cancel the request or change its priority.
